  apply lemma_2_1
  all_goals
    nlinarith [show I.T₀ ≥ 1 by nlinarith [show I.T₀ ≥ 100 by nlinarith [show I.T₀ = 30610046000 by simp [I]; norm_num]]]]
```

Now we combine these inequalities to get the final result. 

First, we know $\sum_{0 < \gamma < I.T_0} 1/\gamma < I.S_0$. 
Second, we know $\sum_{I.T_0 < \gamma < I.T_0 + (V - I.T_0)} 1/\gamma \leq I.B_1(I.T_0, I.T_0 + (V - I.T_0))$. 
The total sum is $\sum_{0 < \gamma < I.T_0 + (V - I.T_0)} 1/\gamma = \sum_{0 < \gamma < I.T_0} 1/\gamma + \sum_{I.T_0 < \gamma < I.T_0 + (V - I.T_0)} 1/\gamma$. 

So $\sum_{0 < \gamma < I.T_0 + (V - I.T_0)} 1/\gamma < I.S_0 + I.B_1(I.T_0, I.T_0 + (V - I.T_0))$.

```tactics
